-- Wall Street fear gauge tops 40, 1st time since May '10
-- 
-- Mon Aug 8, 2011 10:40am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2011/08/08/us-stocks-options-vix-idUSTRE77735V20110808

 

 NEW YORK  (Reuters) - The CBOE Volatility Index, Wall Street's so-called fear gauge, hit 40 for the first time since May 2010 on Monday. 

 The index was up 25.4 percent at 40.12 in the morning session. (Reporting by  Angela Moon , Editing by)